    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Compile a weekly summary with Google Drive and Microsoft Teams in real time\n\n**Pattern:** Scheduled Digest · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nCompile a weekly summary with Google Drive and Microsoft Teams in real time. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual escalations is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Read Recent from Google Drive → Newest First → Trim to Digest Size → Summarize Content (AI) → Post Digest to Microsoft Teams → Confirm All Sends → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to scheduled digest without manual effort\n- Anyone automating escalations in software development\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Notion integration token; OpenAI API key.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "b88e9fa4-102b-6399-68ff-f62615c66014",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -320
      ],
      "id": "37add318-df6f-56c7-d7c1-24be21aec307",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -320
      ],
      "id": "3e34f51d-0f91-49cc-e489-15193e20ff8c",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        610,
        -320
      ],
      "id": "58a33492-e37b-8475-1790-4f631763fd9c",
      "name": "🧹 Data quality"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your escalations process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
